We have photographed many newlywed boat rides…but this was new and different! 

JP took a pre-ceremony ride with his boys…and arrived back on the dock, just in time to walk down the isle and marry his beautiful bride. 

Loved this unique addition to their wedding day. 🛥️ 🤍
A winter wedding from a few years back. ❄️ One that stood out so much with its chic elements and unique color combo…it inspired multiple of my brides the following year. 🤍

I asked a recent groom how married life was. His response…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“Being married is very grounding.” 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I can’t think of a more perfect word to describe marriage. It’s a secure place. It’s living in the present moment, with the reassurance that you’re in all of this together.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Weddings are about so much more than just one day. They are a celebration of one of the most beautiful gifts life has to offer us…commitment.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I am continually reminded of how lucky I am that I get to capture these incredible moments — over and over again. What can I say, I love weddings! 🤍💍

Sunset stroll and a tent under the stars. Everything about this wedding said romance. 🤍

We hike and explore all the time during engagement sessions…but it’s not as often that I get to take a couple in their wedding clothing to experience some of the most beautiful sites Tahoe has to offer. Loved every minute of this session with this adventure loving couple!

I was going to caption this set with something about Spring. But then I thought…for someone who hates talking about the weather, I sure talk about it a lot on here! 

The truth is, I would much prefer to sit down one on one, and get to know YOU. I crave conversations that dig deeper. I love celebrating with others, and mourning with them. I find it hard to connect through an app. And, maybe in some ways, I’m revolting against this new virtual world we live in.

Yet, I do know that sometimes I need to show up with more than a tagline. So today, I just want to say — thank you for being here. Thank you for trusting me to capture your wedding, for your likes, comments, and support. Although, I don’t say it enough, it really means a lot. 🙏🏼

I’m so fortunate to be able to capture these beautiful moments in life, and I love being able to share them with you! 🤍

More and more of my couples are following their vows with a romantic sunset boat ride on the lake. It’s time to sneak away as newlyweds, and soak in the moment. I always snap some pictures, and then hide away to allow my couples that essential time together.

How much time should you schedule for wedding party, family, and couple portraits? I’ll take as much time as I can get… 😉 but ideally, you’ll want to plan a minimum of an hour during the first look or cocktail hour. In addition, I love to sneak my couples away for a 15 to 20 minutes during the reception — for a romantic sunset session, just the two of you. 🤍

As we jumped into the new season this past weekend, Derek and I were reminded of how much we LOVE weddings.

Of how deeply we appreciate the commitment of marriage — embarking on life together, facing the ups and downs as a team. 

We are constantly touched by the beautiful relationships between family and friends, and the expressions of gratitude for each other.

Weddings are a culmination of many of the best things in life, bundled into one very special day — and we can’t help but leave each and every wedding, very tired, 😉 but grateful and strengthened in our own marriage and relationships. 🤍

“Mom, do you think I’ll look this beautiful on my wedding day?”

Words from my 10 year old daughter as she sat behind me and watched me edit these images.

It reminded me that, yes, we really do dream about this day our entire lives. We picture every detail in our minds. We imagine the joy that will be felt in this moment. 

I’m the lucky one, with the important task to bring that picture to reality. 

My hope is that every single one of my brides look at photos of themselves on their wedding day, and feel more beautiful than ever. That it’s a full circle moment — with memories of the little girl they once were and the dreams they’ve now realized. 🤍

Love this set with three generations of beautiful mamas and their daughters!

They were dropped off at their welcome event and greeted at the dock by their closest friends and family. It was an incredible entrance with so much energy and emotion. 🤍 Keep an eye out for more from Coco and Ryan’s beautiful wedding…I’ll be posting soon!

Interrupting my typical feed full of Lake Tahoe backdrops, to share this beautiful summer wedding down in Simi Valley, California. ☀️ It was a fun change of pace, and I absolutely loved getting to see this family again (I photographed the Bride’s sister’s wedding in Tahoe a few years ago).

Congratulations to the incredible, Jamie & Greg! 💍
A sweet and simple elopement. 💍 🤍 I first met this beautiful couple when they were expecting their son. It was amazing to capture that exciting time, and all the big moments since.

Nature's masterpiece: a green floral arch with pristine white blooms — it captivated all eyes, and gracefully melded into the backdrop at the same time.
🌿🌲🤍

Subtle pastels and the delicate bow detail on the heels- a perfect pairing for a whimsical Tahoe wedding. 🤍
First time back to Lake Tahoe since they honeymooned here years ago. 🤍 These images celebrate their love and the distance they’ve traveled together since they last walked these shores.
A memorable exit in a vintage red Cadillac. ❤️ It followed an intimate ceremony surrounded by just the trees and their favorite few people.
Forever one of my favorite bridal looks. 🤍 This fashion forward bride paired a classic and simple wedding gown with two statement pieces — bold earrings and a tulle puff sleeve. 👌🏼

Radiant and ready. 💍 This is always one of my favorite moments of the day. Anticipation is running high, and there is a breath of “this is really happening” just as the bride completes her finishing touches.

I thought I had seen all the breathtaking views of Tahoe…until I saw this one.

A nostalgic private community tucked away on the East Shore, Glenbrook is the oldest settlement on Lake Tahoe. 

What made it an even more special — the bride’s family has a cabin in Glenbrook, that has been in the family for generations. She grew up having bbq’s on the very beach we photographed their newlywed portraits at sunset.

Congratulations Allison and Daniel. 🤍
Thankful. 🤍

This beautiful couple tied the knot (just the two of them) last week in their hometown near Nashville, and then headed west to beautiful Lake Tahoe to celebrate their marriage and document it. 💍 

These were just one of a two part elopement session. A dramatic Tahoe mountain overlook is coming next with these two lovebirds. Double tap if you want to see more. 🤍

Just sent off two beautiful wedding gallery’s, which makes me completely caught up on editing for the first time since April. What a feeling! 🙌🏼 I’ll enjoy it for the next 48 hours before photographing back to back shoots this weekend. 🥰

As I head to another dramatic Lake Tahoe overlook for a wedding in the snow covered trees today…I couldn’t help but think of this pretty elopement. 🌲It’s no wonder people travel to get married here from all over the world, it’s the most magical place. 🤍
Happy Wedding Day to this beautiful couple! Emily is a friend and fellow wedding vendor, a talented planner…so this Christmas weekend wedding is an extra special one. Let’s do this! 🙌🏼 ❤️
Nothing says iconic “Tahoe” like these giant boulders that span across the North Shore. This is one of my top chosen locations for an engagement session, and for good reason. 🙌🏼
